Selenium provides different types of locators to identify web elements such as id, name,
className, tagName, linkText, partialLinkText, CSS selector, and XPath.



driver.findElement(By.id("username")); // id is fatest locator 

driver.findElement(By.name("email"));
driver.findElement(By.className("login-button"));

driver.findElement(By.tagName("input"));
driver.findElement(By.linkText("Login"));
driver.findElement(By.partialLinkText("Log"));
driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("#username"));
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@id='username']"));
